               <msContents resp="#VD">
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Canon_Liturg_319-item1" n="1" class="#liturgica">
                     <title type="desc" key="work_14469">Gregorian fused Sacramentary</title>
                     <msItem n="A">
                        <note>Order of the gradual (fol. 1v), consisting of a combined temporale and
                           sanctorale, and a series of Alleluias per circulum anni, ending with those
                           of the common; kalendar (fol. 15v), entitled martyrologium per circulum anni,
                           with additional obits, among others of the 11th century patriarchs of
                           Aquleia; oratio sancti Ambrosii ante missam (fol. 24), followed by other prayers,
                           apologiae and votive masses (fol. 27v) written by later scribes.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem n="B">
                        <note>Sacramentary (fol. 29v) with the baptism service on Holy Saturday (fol. 85),
                           preceded by the canon and followed (fol. 179) by votive masses for each day of
                           the week; orationes pro peccatis (fol. 181), cotidiane orationes (184v),
                           orationes matutinales and vespettinales (fol. 188v), a long series of votive
                           masses (fol. 192), several of which with epistle, gospel and the opening words of
                           the parts to be sung by the choir; the original ends with the obsequium
                           circa morientes with rubries (fol. 257). A later hand added some prefaces (fol. 263v).
                           None of the saints proper to Reichenau occur in this part. </note>
                     </msItem>
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
