                  <provenance>The volume may have belonged to <persName role="formerOwner" key="person_35650452">Eberhard of Augsburg</persName>, who became
                     patriarch of Aquileia in 1045; his obit is added in the kalendar against 13
                     November (1049). In the kalendar are the Dedicatio aecclesiae sanctae Mariae (29
                     March) and the Dedicatio S. Nicolai (17 Dec.). The only obit written by the
                        scribe is of Henricus Marchio.</provenance>
                  <provenance resp="#PA">At <placeName key="place_7005553">Aquileau</placeName> in the 11th century: obits of the patriarch John (1019), of Poppo (1044), of Henry III (1056) and of Gotobald (1063) in the calendar.</provenance>
